I"”<p>Detecting Internet Explorer is an important part of some projects, especially when implementing any kind of progressive enhancement technique. Unfortunately, <a href="https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/ieinternals/2013/09/21/internet-explorer-11s-many-user-agent-strings/">Microsoft changes the User Agent string to make it look ike something else</a>. Hereâ€™s a quick workaround to detect IE:</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kd">function</span> <span class="nx">isIE</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">ua</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">window</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nb">navigator</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">userAgent</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="c1">//Check the userAgent property of the window.navigator object</span>
  <span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">msie</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">ua</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">indexOf</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">MSIE </span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">);</span> <span class="c1">// IE 10 or older</span>
  <span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">trident</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">ua</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">indexOf</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">Trident/</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">);</span> <span class="c1">//IE 11</span>
  <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">msie</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span> <span class="o">||</span> <span class="nx">trident</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
